<br>
Now with high cha, your lull resists don't mean much, since the mob doesn't aggro on a resist very often.  But it does mean taking more time to recast until lull sticks, etc.  It's much easier to either mezz split, or pull them out and wait on pathing, or simply take 2 to 3 mobs to camp and mezz them there if absolutely necessary (or if incredibly tired and fuzzy on things).  On hard, it doesn't seem like there are that many areas where more than 2 or 3 would come at once anyway, and most of the time those mobs are rootable.  idk, I haven't done that many ldon dungeons, so maybe I'm talking out of my ass.  ;p<br>
<br>
In short, a good fd class is more than adequate as a puller in ldon.  Basically (like in most ele planes things), anyone can pull as long as you have a way to abort your mistakes without killing your group.<br>
<br>
just my opinion! <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://webpages.charter.net/vespae/demon.gif"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:xx-small;"><br>
