I would say this was true before last night (Monday).  But I was in a group with 3 mages, 1 bst, 1 cleric, 1 tank.  We had several times that we faught 7-8 mobs each time (lvl 65 group, normal setting).  The pets just plow them like crazy.  Normally I'd think gate in that situation, but that group just kill them all time after time.  60 mobs in 31 minutes isn't bad at all. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sauriasoulfarer>Sauria Soulfarer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 327<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(10/2/03 8:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4564.topic&index=33>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.antondwer.org.uk/sigpic_18.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Not Intended for LDoN</span><hr size=1> I agree that a well-played member of any pulling class will outperform the best class for a given task if played poorly.  That's a given.  And while this thread could easily devolve and get moved to R&amp;F, it seems level enough so far.<br>
<br>
I am entirely reconciled to the fact that Monks aren't necessarily the best pullers in various settings starting with PoP.  We do however have at that point usually about 60 levels of experience actually *pulling* so that does help.  We are used to pulling, we are used to getting pulped, we don't cry and whine about it, it comes with the territory.  You just don't mince up to a god and throw something at him and expect to live unless you are damned lucky.  And at the same time you have instructed your healers not to heal you unless you say so, so they don't train the raid with healer aggro.  You gotta expect to die and die often, and that takes a certain mindset that monks are familiar with.<br>
<br>
Other classes pull well.  At the forest giant fort in PoStorms, a necro can tag with a spell from the hill behind it, and get a named single...but then she's 65 and I'm 57...maybe I will too at that level.<br>
<br>
In LDoN I think if you took the time to get the mobs one at a time you might find yourself running out of time and failing the mission.  I personally found the mobs so close together and the rooms so small and congested that splitting was a PITA.  Bring CC.<br>
<br>
I think what is being missed in all this ClassX &gt;&gt; ClassY &gt;&gt; ClassZ is that pulling for a group or raid doesn't have to be the act of one class or player!<br>
<br>
Take for instance getting down to the Royals in Chardok.  You get to the square hallway where the Prince is and there is a locked door that leads down to the library and eventually the OK and Queen.  Past that locked door are 6 guards who all come as a cluster and if your raid is in one of the hall corners there really isn't distance enough to split, aside from all the spells going off breaking FD.<br>
<br>
Easiest solution...rogue opens door, I move in and feign, call targets in sequence for a Pac'er to assist off me and pac/lull/whatever, then I get up and start pulling.  The caster doesn't get creamed, I don't get creamed, the raid doesn't get trained, the room is cleared fast and we keep moving.<br>
<br>
pooling your class and player skills to best result &gt;&gt;&gt; class one-upmanship.<br>
